MarkdownCodeBlock.code_block: Cohort and period: This headline gives the type of cohort. Here "2-day period" means that we will look at the behavior of users over 2 days, Users that arrived over a period of 2 days, and whether they connect in the following blocks of 2 days. The example above considers the activity of users between the 21st and 22nd of November.

This gives the retention rate over the 21 and 22 of November for the users arriving in 19 and 20 of November. Here we had 1 active user between the 21st and 22nd, over the 3 that were new users between the 19th and 20th.

This visual indicator gives the same information as above represented graphically. (The third of the circle is from the 33% number.) The color gives additional information: Green indicates this number is growing from the previous calculation. Yellow means stable, and red means decreasing.
This indicates the values used for the calculation.
This is a Sparkline of the history of the retention values. It allows you to see the values in the past to have a broad view of how it evolved.
